# Frontend known issues (CSS / SCSS / LESS)

## Select2 dropdown scrolling (avoid double scrollbars)

Select2 dropdown markup typically includes:

- `.select2-results` (wrapper)
- `.select2-results__options` (scrollable list)

Rules:

- **Do NOT set `overflow-y: scroll` or `overflow-y: auto` on `.select2-results`** if `.select2-results__options` also scrolls; it creates a double scrollbar.
- Preferred: keep scrolling on `.select2-results__options` only.
- When debugging, always check the final merged CSS and DevTools computed rules (specificity / cascade order).
